
# persistence

## concurrency
- label: simultaneous rm of source and target Records with link and unlink operations on their pair either report committed success or a not-found failure, never report database lock or post-commit hook lookup errors, leave no dangling affected Links, and persist Hook Runs for committed link and unlink mutations whose source Record snapshot matched a Hook
  id: lrm
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh concurrent_link_record_disappearance_races
  tags: [implemented]
- label: simultaneous or post-commit deletion of a linked source Record after committed set and unset mutations does not make link-predicate Hooks fail or error; committed set and unset mutations evaluate Hook Queries against a mutation-time Record and Link snapshot, and when a concurrent deletion lands before the Link snapshot is captured the Hook legitimately skips, so each committed mutation persists either one matching Hook Run or none
  id: sls
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh concurrent_set_unset_link_snapshot_races
  tags: [implemented]
- label: create Hooks evaluate link predicates against an empty create-time Link snapshot, and rm Hooks evaluate link predicates against the pre-delete Link snapshot so post-event Link changes do not make matching Hooks skip or non-matching Hooks run
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh create_rm_link_snapshot_hooks
  tags: [implemented]
- label: simultaneous hook add and hook rm with matching create mutations finish without database lock errors or post-commit hook persistence failures, leave removed Hooks absent and added Hooks present, and persist Hook Runs for Hooks already selected by committed mutations even if those Hooks are removed before the run is recorded
  id: hkr
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh concurrent_hook_lifecycle_races
  tags: [implemented]
- label: simultaneous hook rm with already-selected set, unset, rm, link, and unlink mutations finishes without database lock errors or post-commit Hook persistence failures, removes the Hooks from hook ls, and persists Hook Runs for each committed mutation selected before removal
  id: hmr
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh concurrent_hook_lifecycle_mutation_races
  tags: [implemented]
- label: simultaneous hook add and hook rm churn while hook ls and ctx read the Store finishes without database lock errors or panics, keeps every hook ls output parseable and in registration order, keeps every ctx output within the Quick Context contract, and leaves final Hook counts consistent with successful adds and removals
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh concurrent_hook_churn_reads
  tags: [implemented]
